Package org.apache.beam.sdk.extensions.sql

BeamSQL provides a new interface to run a SQL statement with Beam.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    BeamSqlSeekableTable
    A seekable table converts a JOIN operator to an inline lookup.
    BeamSqlTable
    This interface defines a Beam Sql Table.
    BeamSqlUdf
    Interface to create a UDF in Beam SQL.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BeamSql
    BeamSql is the DSL interface of BeamSQL.
    BeamSqlCli
    BeamSqlCli provides methods to execute Beam SQL with an interactive client.
    QueryTransform
    A PTransform representing an execution plan for a SQL query.
    RowHelper
    Atomic Coders for Row fields for SQL types.
    RowHelper.BooleanCoder
    Coder for Java type Boolean.
    RowHelper.DateCoder
    Coder for Java type Date, it's stored as Long.
    RowHelper.DoubleCoder
    Coder for Java type Double, it's stored as BigDecimal.
    RowHelper.FloatCoder
    Coder for Java type Float, it's stored as BigDecimal.
    RowHelper.ShortCoder
    Coder for Java type Short.
    RowHelper.TimeCoder
    Coder for Java type GregorianCalendar, it's stored as Long.
    RowSqlType
    Type builder for Row with SQL types.
    RowSqlType.Builder
    Builder class to construct RowType.
    SqlRowTypeFactory
    For internal use only; no backwards-compatibility guarantees.
    SqlTypeCoder
    Base class for coders for supported SQL types.
    SqlTypeCoders
    Coders for SQL types supported in Beam.
